<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77f25e24-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ccc"><num value="460ccc">§ 460ccc.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of this subchapter, the term—</chapeau><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id77f25e25-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ccc/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> “conservation area” means the Red Rock Canyon National Conservation Area established pursuant to <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s460ccc–1">section 460ccc–1 of this title</ref>;</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id77f25e26-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ccc/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> “public lands” has the meaning stated in <ref href="/us/usc/t43/s1702/e">section 1702(e) of title 43</ref>; and</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id77f25e27-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ccc/c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content> “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id77f25e28-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/621/s2">Pub. L. 101–621, § 2</ref>, <date date="1990-11-16">Nov. 16, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/3342">104 Stat. 3342</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id77f25e29-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id77f25e2a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="shortTitle" id="id77f25e2b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Short Title</heading><p><ref href="/us/pl/101/621/s1">Pub. L. 101–621, § 1</ref>, <date date="1990-11-16">Nov. 16, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/3342">104 Stat. 3342</ref>, provided that: <quotedContent origin="/us/pl/101/621/s1">“This Act [enacting this subchapter] may be cited as the ‘Red Rock Canyon National Conservation Area Establishment Act of 1990’.”</quotedContent>
</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
